In XMLJUnitFormatter.java and PlainJUnitFormatter.java is a bug, which throws
ClassCastException when running tests implementing directly junit.framework.Test
interface. 

In method startTest instead of:

currentTest.setAttribute(ATTR_NAME, ((TestCase) t).name());

there should be something like this:

if (t instanceof TestCase) {
    currentTest.setAttribute(ATTR_NAME, ((TestCase) t).name());
} else {
    currentTest.setAttribute(ATTR_NAME, ("Unknown");
}


The same thing also applies to the plain text formatter.
